/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/planner-chains/chain-05.md:16:This is the only chain whose main object is the localization package itself. It does not treat Lagrangian or tube-adapted coordinates as harmless setup; it audits whether the package change is the source of the apparent gain.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/planner-chains/chain-05.md:23:- Action: state exactly why the neutral Eulerian package from `step-004` may have been too weak and what new package is being proposed, such as Lagrangian, tube-following, or another sharply defined adapted localization.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/planner-chains/chain-05.md:25:- Expected output: a package memo naming the new localization, its claimed advantage, and the precise boundary of what this branch is allowed to claim.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/planner-chains/chain-05.md:49:- Action: keep the comparator package in view to detect fake gains caused only by relocalization.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:5:This chain is strongest as an obstruction hunt and weak as a positive proof route. Its good instinct is that full 3D Navier-Stokes transports more structure than energy alone, and that same-helicity folklore should not be confused with theorem-relevant leverage. Its main weakness is that it treats "joint energy-helicity flux" as if it were already a candidate coercive mechanism. It is not. Energy is positive and directly tied to standard control. Helicity is sign-indefinite, scale-weighted, and highly vulnerable to cancellation. Unless the chain can produce a one-sided, localization-stable, endpoint-relevant gain from that coupling, it is mostly repackaging cascade geometry.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:7:The likely honest output is therefore a sharp negative memo: the coupled invariant structure is exact but too non-coercive, too prior-art-adjacent, or too fragile under mixed-helicity restoration and localization to move a real continuation or blowup bottleneck.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:16:- The allowed packages are too heterogeneous. Coarse-grained local balances, dyadic fluxes, and other ledgers do not merely present the same object differently; they expose different cancellation patterns and different localization debts. Treating them as interchangeable "packages" creates room for decomposition shopping.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:27:- Writing the energy and helicity transfer identities is easy relative to the real problem. The hard question is whether any coupled identity yields a one-sided estimate after all admissible signs and localizations are restored. The chain risks mistaking "I have an exact balance law" for "I have isolated a usable mechanism."
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:33:Failure mode: Step 2 exports a clean "coupled-flux memo" whose distinguishing feature is either decomposition-specific or non-coercive once signs, absolute values, and localization are paid honestly.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:65:- The negative menu is sensible but too clean. The route may fail for several reasons at once: no one-sided quantity, prior-art collapse, mixed-helicity restoration, and localization failure. Forcing a single typed obstruction can underreport how overdetermined the failure really is.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:74:That is the central risk. Energy has positivity and robust localization tools. Helicity does not. Pairing them does not automatically create a stronger monotone quantity, and the chain never forces that issue early enough.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:99:- Step 4 at least names the real debts: mixed-helicity restoration, low-helicity regions, viscosity, and localization.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:105:This is a respectable negative-audit chain and a weak positive chain. Its best contribution is to force a serious answer to a useful question: does exact energy-helicity coupling ever yield a one-sided, localization-stable gain on a named Navier-Stokes bottleneck, or does it collapse into sign-sensitive but non-coercive cascade bookkeeping? My expectation is that the latter is the honest answer.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:107:So the chain is worth running only if it is understood as a short route to a calibrated no-go. If it tries to become a proof program before exhibiting a precise coercive quantity that survives mixed-helicity restoration and localization, it will mostly manufacture elegant invariant rhetoric around a structurally weak idea.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:7:The problem is that the chain is still structurally biased toward finding a "distinguished" symbol-level feature before it has earned a theorem-level bottleneck. In practice, the helical-triad literature is already full of exact-looking interaction geometry that becomes weak, non-sign-definite, or irrelevant once one restores mixed triads, shell summation, and localization. So the positive route here is weak; the negative route is much stronger. If this chain produces anything honest, it is more likely to be a sharp obstruction memo than a usable regularity mechanism.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:31:The kill condition is again too permissive. A feature can survive as genuinely Tao-sensitive and still be useless because its quantitative effect is far below summation and localization losses. This step should not just sort structure into bins; it should estimate the maximal plausible size of the effect.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:44:### Step 4 - Stress-test summation, localization, and robustness
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:49:- Localization is a serious threat that the chain mentions too lightly. Helical-triad structure is most transparent in global Fourier variables. Many of the hoped-for cancellations are not stable under spatial cutoffs, local energy identities, or profile decompositions. If the eventual theorem bottleneck needs localization, this step is not a side check; it is the main obstacle.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:60:- "State the first missing lemma" can hide the actual impossibility. In these problems, the first missing lemma is often the whole problem: a sign-definite shell-summed estimate, a coercive bound after localization, or a frequency-envelope gain that does not exist.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:61:- The negative branch is much more credible than the positive branch. A careful memo saying "exact helical geometry creates triad-level preferences, but they are quantitatively annihilated by mixed-triad summation and localization" would be a real output. A positive proposition here would require a very unusual piece of structure, and the chain has not given reason to expect one.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:75:What is genuinely strong here is the discipline. The chain names the object, insists on one bottleneck, and explicitly forces summation/localization stress tests. That is good design.
