/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-012/GOAL.md:183:  regularity.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:15:- "Define exactly what counts as preserved by Tao averaging and destroyed by Tao averaging" is only meaningful after fixing the level of comparison. Is the chain comparing identities, transport laws, closure estimates, compactness-compatible quantities, or actual contradiction mechanisms? Those are different tests. A property can fail as an exact identity and still survive at the estimate level that matters for regularity.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:26:- The candidate examples already preload the outcome: commutator-ready scalarization, deformation constraints, stochastic circulation, vorticity-direction persistence, pressure/stress identity. Those are familiar mission motifs, not a neutral search over "exact NS structures." The chain says "for example," but examples shape selection in practice.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:73:The chain says it wants "operational" exact properties, not just Tao-sensitive ones. But the workflow still lets Tao discrimination set the agenda before theorem-facing leverage is established. That is dangerous because many exact NS features are genuinely scrambled by averaging and still useless for regularity.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:17:- The endpoint choices are too coarse. "Localized regularity," "continuation criterion," and "concentration exclusion" have very different burdens. A commutator that helps in a continuation criterion may be useless for localization once cutoff commutators and pressure recovery are inserted. Freezing only the endpoint family does not prevent later goalpost shifting.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:48:- If the endpoint is localized regularity or concentration exclusion, cutoff commutators and pressure localization are not "cleanup"; they are often the whole game. The chain says to include them immediately, which is good, but it does not acknowledge that this will usually erase any formal commutator gain found in Step 2.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:49:- "Write one explicit inequality" is necessary but insufficient. A line can be explicit and still be useless if it imports a stronger norm than the endpoint can afford. The real question is whether the inequality closes with the regularity class already available, not whether one can symbolically place the commutator into the argument.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:59:- The criterion "narrower than arbitrary finite-energy regularity" is too weak. Many useless lemmas are narrower than full regularity while still being effectively equivalent to the hard case. For example, "control one compensated scalar with enough regularity to reconstruct all bad NS terms" is formally narrower but substantively the same problem.
